Whatsapp Analytics

Pre-Processing

Read in text file as large character vector and transform into data frame. Then process data frame to extract time stamp, user name and message.

library(stringr)
library(data.table)
library(lubridate)
library(ggplot2)
library(shiny)
library(scales)
setwd("C:/dev/R")
# Source file path
inputFile <- "whatsapp.txt"
# read in file as large vector
textLines <- readLines(con = inputFile)
# transform to data frame
df <- as.data.frame(textLines)
df$textLines <- as.character(df$textLines)
# regex pattern
pattern <- "([0-9]{1,2}/[0-9]{1,2}/[0-9]{1,2}, [0-9]{1,2}:[0-9]{1,2} - ){1}([a-zA-Z0-9 ](.*?)(:))"
df_str <- data.frame(TS = as.POSIXct(character()),
                        Name = character(),
                        Msg = character(),
                        stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
# restructure data frame
for(i in 1:nrow(df)) {
  #cat(paste0(df[i,1],"\n"))
  if(str_detect(df[i,1], pattern)) {
    
    # get location of ts + name pattern
    loc <- str_locate(df[i,1],pattern)[2]
    
    # extract time stamp + name and then split string
    extr_ts_name <- str_extract(df[i,1],pattern)
    split_ts_name <- str_split(extr_ts_name, " - ")
    
    # extract time stamp
    extr_ts <- as.POSIXct(strptime(unlist(split_ts_name)[1],"%m/%d/%y, %H:%M"))
    
    # extract name
    extr_name <- gsub(":","",unlist(split_ts_name)[2])
    
    # extract message from end of name to end of string
    extr_msg <- substr(df[i,1],loc+1,nchar(df[i,1]))
    
    # cat(paste0("TS: ",extr_ts,"\n"))
    # cat(paste0("Name: ",extr_name,"\n"))
    # cat(paste0("Message: ",extr_msg,"\n"))
    
    df_str[i,1] <- extr_ts
    df_str[i,2] <- extr_name
    df_str[i,3] <- extr_msg
    
    } 
  else {
    # add line to msg
    df_str[i,3] <- df[i,1]
  }
}
# Delete na msg rows
df_str <- df_str[df_str$Msg != "",]
# for each row, if time stamp is NA then fill in previous time stamp and name
for(i in 1:nrow(df_str)) {
  if(is.na(df_str[i,1])) {
    df_str[i,1] <- df_str[i-1,1]
    df_str[i,2] <- df_str[i-1,2]
  }
}
# Replace Names
df_str$Name <- gsub("Alok Chitnis","Alok",df_str$Name)
df_str$Name <- ifelse(grepl("Eeshan",df_str$Name), "Eeshan", df_str$Name)
df_str$Name <- gsub("Varun Ajmera","Varun",df_str$Name)
df_str$Name <- gsub(" CASE","",df_str$Name)
# Remove special characters
df_str$Msg <- iconv(df_str$Msg, "latin1", "ASCII", sub="")
df_str_o <- df_str
#head(df_str)
Add additional variables
df_str <- df_str_o
# get day
df_str$Day <- as.Date(df_str$TS)
# get hour
df_str$Hour <- as.POSIXlt(df_str$TS)$hour
# get year
df_str$Year <- year(df_str$Day)
# get month
df_str$Month <- as.Date(cut(df_str$Day, breaks = "month"))
# get week
df_str$Week <- as.Date(cut(df_str$Day, breaks = "week", start.on.monday = TRUE))
# word count per message
df_str$WC <- str_count(df_str$Msg, "\\S+")
# aggregations
df_dt <- as.data.table(df_str)

Messages by User - since 2nd July 2016

df_ts_user <- df_dt[,list(MsgCount = length(Msg),
                          AvgWordCount = mean(WC),
                          MessagesPerDay = length(Msg)/length(unique(df_dt$Day)))
                    ,by=c("Name")]
df_ts_user$AvgWordCount <- round(df_ts_user$AvgWordCount, 1)
df_ts_user$MessagesPerDay <- round(df_ts_user$MessagesPerDay, 1)
df_ts_user$Percent_Of_Total <- round((df_ts_user$MsgCount/sum(df_ts_user$MsgCount))*100,1)

Word Clouds


# Install
# install.packages("tm")  # for text mining
# install.packages("SnowballC") # for text stemming
# install.packages("wordcloud") # word-cloud generator 
# install.packages("RColorBrewer") # color palettes
#library(devtools)
#install_url("https://cran.r-project.org/src/contrib/Archive/slam/slam_0.1-37.tar.gz")
# Load
library(tm)
library(SnowballC)
library(wordcloud)

generateWordCloud <- function(docs) {
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function (x , pattern ) gsub(pattern, " ", x))
  docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "/")
  docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "@")
  docs <- tm_map(docs, toSpace, "\\|")
  
  # Convert the text to lower case
  docs <- tm_map(docs, content_transformer(tolower))
  # Remove numbers
  docs <- tm_map(docs, removeNumbers)
  # Remove english common stopwords
  docs <- tm_map(docs, removeWords, stopwords("english"))
  # Remove your own stop word
  # specify your stopwords as a character vector
  docs <- tm_map(docs, removeWords, c("media", "omitted","Y","will","yeah"
                                      ,"http","https","www","hai","hain","kya")) 
  # Remove punctuations
  docs <- tm_map(docs, removePunctuation)
  # Eliminate extra white spaces
  docs <- tm_map(docs, stripWhitespace)
  # Text stemming
  # docs <- tm_map(docs, stemDocument)
  
  dtm <- TermDocumentMatrix(docs)
  m <- as.matrix(dtm)
  v <- sort(rowSums(m),decreasing=TRUE)
  d <- data.frame(word = names(v),freq=v)
  
  set.seed(1111)
  wordcloud(words = d$word, freq = d$freq, scale = c(3,0.5), min.freq = 5,
            max.words=150, random.order=FALSE, rot.per=0, 
            colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"))
  
  d$Percent_Of_Total <- round((d$freq/sum(d$freq))*100,1)
  
}
